XIIdigitation, n.:
	The practice of trying to determine the year a movie was made
	by deciphering the Roman numerals at the end of the credits.
		-- Rich Hall, "Sniglets"


Code rot -- mostly caused by people redefining "fresh".
		-- Wes Peters


